Session conducted by Akmar Nafi
CSS styles our content specified in HTML
It can be included within <style> tags
It comprises of using selectors which are basically the tags on html where we want to include our styling
div{} means styling <div> tags on HTML .
One such styling is background-color which when written under a selector provides it with a specified color
A color can be specified by either saying the name or a hexacode or rgb code.
Its width and height can be specified by pixels or percentages
A certain tag can be selected by further specifications such as id and class
A Box model was later talked about
It involved spacings which can be adjusted by the attributes border,margin and padding.
